# NewKnowledgeAPI Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Knowledge Management API built with ASP.NET Core (.NET 8) that provides a sophisticated Q&A system with AI-powered semantic search capabilities using OpenAI embeddings and Azure Cosmos DB.

## Code Style and Conventions

### C# Conventions
- Use PascalCase for public members, types, and methods
- Use camelCase for private fields and local variables
- Prefix interfaces with 'I' (e.g., IQuestionService)
- Use 'Async' suffix for async methods
- Use explicit types instead of 'var' when type isn't obvious
- Follow Microsoft C# coding conventions

### Architecture Patterns
- Follow Repository pattern for data access (DbService)
- Use Service layer for business logic
- Keep controllers thin - delegate to services
- Use DTOs for API responses, separate from domain models
- Follow RESTful API design principles

### Naming Conventions
- Controllers: {Entity}Controller (e.g., QuestionController)
- Services: {Entity}Service (e.g., QuestionService)
- DTOs: {Entity}Dto (e.g., QuestionDto)
- Extended DTOs: {Entity}DtoEx (e.g., QuestionDtoEx)
- Domain Models: Plain names (e.g., Question, Answer)

### Project Structure
```
/
├── A/                    # Answers domain
│   ├── Answers/         # Answer entities and services
│   └── Groups/          # Group entities and services
├── Q/                    # Questions domain
│   ├── Questions/       # Question entities and services
│   └── Categories/      # Category entities and services
├── History/             # User interaction tracking
├── Services/            # Shared services (DB, OpenAI, Vector Search)
├── Common/              # Shared models and utilities
└── Models/              # Additional models (e.g., EmbeddedQuestion)
```

### Database (Cosmos DB) Conventions
- Use partition keys consistently (e.g., "kind" property)
- Include "id" and "_etag" for all documents
- Use hierarchical data modeling for parent-child relationships
- Store embeddings as float arrays in dedicated properties

### API Design
- Use attribute routing: [Route("api/[controller]")]
- Support pagination where appropriate
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes
- Use [Authorize] attribute for protected endpoints
- Include proper error handling and logging

### Vector Search & AI Integration
- Generate embeddings for all searchable content
- Cache embeddings to reduce API calls
- Use cosine similarity for vector search
- Store embeddings alongside original content
- Handle OpenAI API errors gracefully

### Testing Approach
- Write unit tests for services
- Use xUnit for testing framework
- Mock external dependencies (Cosmos DB, OpenAI)
- Test vector search accuracy with sample queries
- Validate embedding generation and storage

### Security Best Practices
- Never commit API keys or connection strings
- Use Azure Key Vault or environment variables for secrets
- Validate all input data
- Use parameterized queries
- Implement proper authentication and authorization

### Performance Considerations
- Use caching for frequently accessed data
- Implement efficient Cosmos DB queries with proper indexing
- Batch embedding generation when possible
- Use async/await throughout the application
- Monitor and optimize vector search performance

### Common Tasks
- To add a new entity: Create model, DTO, service, and controller
- To add vector search: Generate embeddings, store in Cosmos DB, implement similarity search
- To track history: Use HistoryService to record user interactions
- To add caching: Use IMemoryCache with appropriate expiration

### Dependencies
- .NET 8.0
- Azure Cosmos DB
- Azure AD Authentication
- OpenAI API (for embeddings)
- Newtonsoft.Json
- Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Memory

### Environment Variables Required
- COSMOS_CONNECTION_STRING
- OPENAI_API_KEY
- AZURE_AD_TENANT_ID
- AZURE_AD_CLIENT_ID

### Debugging Tips
- Check Cosmos DB Explorer for data structure
- Use Postman/Thunder Client for API testing
- Monitor OpenAI API usage and costs
- Check application logs for vector search performance
- Validate JWT tokens for authentication issues